  "text": "The muscarinic agonist pilocarpine is known to activate leg CPGs in isolated 323 nervous systems of arthropods [CITATION_1] interactions, we activated the thoracic CPGs by applying pilocarpine to the metathoracic 330 ganglion alone in an in-vitro preparation, and compared the motor output of the different 331 depressor MN pools both with the SEG intact and following its removal. Thus, while the 332 generation of rhythmicity arose from the caudal end of the ganglia chain, any SEG 333 modulatory influence had to be sent from the rostral end (pictogram: Fig. 2A ). 334",
